	<div id="headline">
		<div class="wrapper">
			<div id="lead">
				<div class="leadbanner">A free, open source tool for complex research problems.</div>
				<div id="leadtext">A software companion to a 30+ year-old CIA research methodology, Open Source Analysis of Competing Hypotheses (ACH)
				will help you think objectively and logically about overwhelming amounts of data and hypotheses. It can also guide research teams 
				toward more productive discussions by identifying the exact points of contention.</div>
				<div id="download"><a href="docs/The_ACH_Methodology_and_Its_Purpose">Learn the methodology</a><br /> 
				<a href="docs/Sample_Projects">View a sample project</a><br />
				<a href="download">Download version 1.0.3alpha</a></div>
			</div>
			<div id="screenshot">
				<a href="docs/Sample_Projects"><img src="images/ach_sample_matrix_narrow2.png"></a>
				<div id="caption">
					ACH has you evaluate each data point in the context of each hypothesis. 
					When finished, a clearer, more structured perspective of the problem emerges.
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
